		recommendation: "Two complementary views with toggle: **View 1 — Small Multiples (default, for precision):** 12 mini line charts, arranged in 3×4 grid. Each: x = months since origination (0-12), y = cumulative inadimplência (%). SAME x-range (0-12) and SAME y-range (0-5%) across ALL multiples. Order: chronological, newest at bottom-right. Gestor scans top-left to bottom-right: if curves get lower → improvement over time. Label: each mini-chart titled with safra (e.g., 'Jan/25'). Last point labeled with current value. **View 2 — Heatmap (toggle, for pattern detection):** Matrix: rows = safras (newest at bottom), columns = months since origination. Color: sequential palette (white = 0%, dark red = 5%+). Patterns visible: diagonal bands = aging effect. Lighter bottom rows = newer safras performing better. Dark spots = anomalous safra-months. **For both views:** (1) Tooltip on any data point: exact value, safra, month, comparison to portfolio average. (2) Annotation: anomalous safras marked with explanation if known. (3) Summary above: 'Safras 2025 outperform 2024 by avg 0.8pp at month 6. Model v2.3 (Sep 2025) showed significant improvement.' (4) Click safra label → drill-down to safra detail (operation list, score distribution, geography). **Implementation:** VintageChart component with mode toggle. Shared data source. Small multiples with linked brushing (hover month 6 on one → highlight month 6 on all)."
		principlesApplied: ["ax-01", "ax-02", "ax-06"]
