limitations: [
	{
		description: "Chart type recommendations assume standard data shapes. Unusual data (extreme outliers, very sparse, highly skewed, heavy-tailed) may require non-standard visualization approaches."
		alternative: "Start with recommended chart type. Validate with actual data. If recommended chart doesn't communicate the pattern clearly (outliers dominate scale, sparse data looks empty, skew hides majority): iterate. Options: log scale for heavy-tailed data, jitter for overplotted scatter, bin width adjustment for sparse histograms. Log exception with reasoning for future reference."
		rationale: "Guidelines are defaults for typical data. Real data is often atypical. Iterate when default doesn't serve."
	},
	{
		description: "Micro-visualizations (sparklines, bullet charts) at very small sizes (60×16px) may be illegible on low-resolution displays or when rendered at sub-pixel precision."
		alternative: "Minimum size constraints in design system: sparkline ≥60×16px, bullet chart ≥100×16px. Test on target devices: construtora's actual monitors (likely 1080p), fornecedor's actual phones (varied quality). If illegible at minimum size: fall back to delta indicator (text-only: '↑8.3%') which has no minimum pixel requirement."
		rationale: "Design for actual devices, not ideal conditions. Graceful degradation: sparkline → delta indicator → plain number."
	},
	{
		description: "Fintech-specific visualizations (vintage analysis, concentration, score gauge) assume domain expertise. New analyst, new construtora user, or auditor may not interpret correctly without guidance."
		alternative: "Inline help per chart: 'ℹ️' icon that reveals: 'Este gráfico mostra [explanation]. Como ler: [guidance]. Cada [element] representa [meaning].' First-time user: onboarding walkthrough highlighting fintech-specific charts with interactive explanation. Help text written by domain expert, not just designer."
		rationale: "Even expert audience has new members. Fintech-specific vis is powerful but requires domain knowledge. Inline help bridges the gap."
	},
	{
		description: "Accessibility for complex visualizations (heatmap, scatter with hundreds of points) is inherently limited — screen readers cannot convey spatial patterns, and redundant encoding for 100+ data points is impractical."
		alternative: "For complex charts: provide accessible alternative — hidden data table (sortable, filterable) that conveys same information in tabular form. ARIA: aria-describedby links to table. Summary text: 'heatmap shows inadimplência by sacado and month. 3 sacados have elevated rates in Q4. See table below for details.' Not every visual nuance translates to text — but key insights must."
		rationale: "100% visual accessibility for complex charts is impossible. Key insight accessibility + alternative data format is achievable and sufficient."
	},
	{
		description: "Chart library standardization (10 chart components in DS) may not cover edge cases — some analyses may need custom visualization (network graph for supply chain, geographic map for regional concentration)."
		alternative: "Standard library covers 90% of needs. For edge cases: evaluate — is custom vis justified by frequency and value? If used >3 times: add to DS. If one-time analysis: custom is acceptable with documentation. Never custom for standard patterns (bar, line, scatter) — always use DS component."
		rationale: "Standard covers standard. Custom for custom. Don't reinvent bar chart. Don't force network graph into standard chart."
	},
]

rationale: "Visualização de dados traduz números em formas visuais que o cérebro processa ordens de magnitude mais rápido que texto. Na Mesh fintech com métricas financeiras, operacionais e de rede, esta lens operacionaliza: marks e channels com eficácia perceptual e preattentive processing (Bertin 1967, Munzner 2014, Cleveland/McGill 1984, channel budget 2023+, Healey 1996), seleção de chart type por pergunta e chart literacy da persona (Schwabish 2021, Few 2012, question-driven 2023+, chart literacy calibration 2024+), sparklines e micro-visualizações para glanceable data em KPI cards e tables (Tufte 2006, Few 2006, micro-visualizations 2023+, glanceable data 2024+), integridade visual contra distorções com lie factor e responsible visualization (Tufte 1983, Few 2012, responsible visualization 2024+), labels/tooltips/annotations como progressive labeling para storytelling visual (Schwabish 2021, progressive labeling 2023+), visualizações fintech-specific como componentes do design system (score gauge, concentration chart, vintage analysis, waterfall, risk scatter, feature importance), acessibilidade com CVD-safe palettes e redundant encoding (WCAG 2.1, redundant encoding 2023+), e small multiples para comparação de cohorts (Tufte 1983, faceted visualization 2022+). Universal na semiótica visual; específica na aplicação a fintech B2B multisided com personas de chart literacy variada."

}
